sentences: Oli tore teiega kohtuda, olen rõõmus, et olete siin.
Palun istuge, me oleme juba sinna joonud.
context: The word 'joonud' is the partitive case form of the verb 'tulema' (to come) in Estonian. It indicates that someone has arrived or come somewhere, and it's used to refer to people who have already arrived. In this context, it could mean 'arrived ones' or simply refer to those present/who have come.
